      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The collection contains correspondence between Faulkner and
         Liveright of the publishing firm Boni and Liveright regarding
         the publication of Mosquitoes and the rejected publication of
         Flags in the Dust, which was eventually published in 1929 by
         Harcourt Brace and Company under the title Sartoris. A novel
         by Isadora Duncan is another topic. Also included is one
         letter, 1949 July 27, from Faulkner to Manuel Komroff.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>This collection is arranged chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
